<section id="quickstart">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <p class="section-label">Get Started</p>
      <h2 class="section-title">15-Minute Setup</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">
        Copy the template into your project, customize the configuration blocks,
        and you're enforcing architecture immediately.
      </p>

      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">1</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Copy the template</h3>
            <div class="terminal">
              <div class="terminal-header">
                <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
                <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
                <span class="terminal-dot"></span>
                <span class="terminal-title">bash</span>
              </div>
              <div class="terminal-body">
                <span class="prompt">$</span> cd /path/to/your/project<br />
                <br />
                <span class="comment"># Copy the .claude directory</span><br />
                <span class="prompt">$</span> cp -r /path/to/claude-code-guardrails/template/.claude .<br />
                <br />
                <span class="comment"># Copy the CLAUDE.md template</span><br />
                <span class="prompt">$</span> cp /path/to/claude-code-guardrails/template/CLAUDE.md .<br />
                <br />
                <span class="comment"># Copy SPEC + memory templates</span><br />
                <span class="prompt">$</span> mkdir -p docs<br />
                <span class="prompt">$</span> cp /path/to/claude-code-guardrails/template/docs/*.md docs/
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">2</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Customize CLAUDE.md</h3>
            <p>Replace the <code>{`{{PLACEHOLDER}}`}</code> markers with your project's values. The file has comments explaining each placeholder.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">3</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Configure hooks</h3>
            <p>Each hook has a <code>// === CONFIGURATION ===</code> block at the top. Edit the constants for your project's APIs, prefixes, and boundaries.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">4</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Create your first SPEC</h3>
            <p>Copy the SPEC template, fill in your actual components, and run <code>/check-drift</code> to verify.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .steps {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 2rem;
    max-width: 700px;
  }

  .step {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    align-items: flex-start;
  }

  .step-number {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 2.5rem;
    height: 2.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--cyan);
    border: 2px solid var(--cyan);
    border-radius: 50%;
  }

  .step-content {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
  }

  .step-content h3 {
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
  }

  .step-content p {
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .step-content .terminal {
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
</style>
